title: SPECTRUM-SPARK Annual Meeting
text:
Held in the backdrop of the RACV Cape Shanck, 100 researchers across the consortia gathered together to talk about the latest in infectious diseases research, including pandemic preparedness, disease surveillance, research software and disease modelling.
Monday saw the early and mid career academics gather for networking, career advice, tips on project management, and some fun storytelling. The evening wrapped up at place, where food and discussion flowed.
On Tuesday and Wednesday, the remainder of the consortia gathered together, with presentations from seed funded projects,
The organising committee consisted of: Nefel Tellioglu, Laura Bannerman, Johanna Monk and TK Le.
